Step 1: Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, the Total Liabilities equal the Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity minus Total Owner's Equity.  
  Total Liabilities = 15,023,526.85 – 14,193,771.08 = 829,755.77  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity = 829,755.77 / 14,193,771.08 ≈ 0.0585  
Rounded to two decimal places, this is approximately 0.06.

Step 2: Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, the Net Profit is 1,193,771.08 and the Total Revenue is 5,695,115.02.  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (1,193,771.08 / 5,695,115.02) × 100 ≈ 20.95%  

Step 3: Return on Assets (ROA)  
• From the balance sheet, the Total Assets at the end date is 15,023,526.85.  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100 = (1,193,771.08 / 15,023,526.85) × 100 ≈ 7.95%

Step 4: Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, the Accounts Receivable at the end is 1,562,598.26 and at the beginning it was 0. Assuming the average accounts receivable = (Beginning + Ending) / 2 = (0 + 1,562,598.26) / 2 ≈ 781,299.13  
• AR Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable = 5,695,115.02 / 781,299.13 ≈ 7.29  

Thus, the solution in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {'Debt to Equity Ratio': '0.06', 'Net Profit Margin': '20.95%', 'Return on Assets (ROA)': '7.95%', 'Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio': '7.29'} }
